   Informat Assoc, Phuket, THAILAND, JUL 05-08, 2022},
Organization = {Inst Elect \& Informat Engineers; Engn Sci Soc \& Elect Soc; Inst Elect
   Informat \& Commun Engineers; Thailand Convent \& and Exhibit Bur;
   Chiang Mai Univ, OASYS Res Grp; Nakhon Pathom Rajabhat Univ; King
   Mongkuts Inst Technol Ladkrabang; Enertronix Co Ltd},
Abstract = {With the COVID-19 epidemic situation, distance and hybrid learning
   happen extensively. As the demand for connectivity has dramatically
   increased, the campus data center operators have been forced to scale
   rapidly and make decisions quickly. A digital twin assists the
   decision-making process by providing a virtual representation of a
   complex system. This paper presents an application of digital twin
   modeling for a data center in an academic institute. The building
   information modeling (BIM) has been applied to represent the data
   center. The sensing data (i.e., temperature, humidity, energy
   consumption, and computing resource utilization) in the data center are
   collected using the network of IoT. These sensing data are visualized
   together with the data center model. Then, the long short-term memory
   (LSTM) technique is applied to predict the future room temperature. The
   real-time data sensing of the data center facilitates the data center
   operator to monitor incidents in the data center.},
